<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9442] Pig tests failing in 2.2 and trunk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9442</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In CQLRecordWriter, we are catching and handling a certain class of exception. Unfortunately, we are still setting lastException, so hadoop reports that the map reduce job has errored out and failed, even though it succeeded. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are also having an occasional issue where the driver returns a different interrupt related exception than what we are checking for. I have moved the check logic out into a separate function, and now check for both.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
